    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1" type="to"
                            >Stalin</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d19fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché Moscow, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-15">July 15,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and secret from the President to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>.</p>
                <p>I am deeply sorry for unfortunate sinking of one of your ships in North Pacific
                    and have directed every possible future precaution.</p>
                <p>Although I have no detailed news, I think I can safely congratulate you on the
                    splendid showing your armies are making against the German offensive at
                    Kursk.</p>
                <p>I hope to hear from you very soon about the other matter which I still feel to be
                    of great importance to you and me.<note n="2" xml:id="d19fn2">A handwritten
                        notation at this point on the source text reads, “In President’s letter to
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> via Amb. <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJE1">Davies</persName>.” For the President’s letter, see
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_3">p. 3</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
